<subsubsection xml:id="subsubsec-mean-grouped">
    <title>Mean (Grouped)</title>
    
    <introduction>
        <p>
            Grouped data is data that has been organized into classes or intervals together with their frequencies. Instead of listing every single value, the observations are arranged into groups to make large data sets easier to analyze.
        </p>
    </introduction>

    <activity>
        <p>
            <term>Work in groups</term>
        </p>
        <p>
            The table below shows the amount of pocket money, in shillings, that parents give to students per week.
        </p>
        <table>
            <title>Pocket Money Distribution</title>
            <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                <row halign="left" header="yes">
                    <cell>Pocket Money (Ksh)</cell>
                    <cell><m>100 - 199</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>200 - 299</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>300 - 399</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>400 - 499</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>500 - 599</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row halign="left" header="yes"> 
                    <cell>Number of students</cell>
                    <cell><m>8</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>15</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>22</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>20</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </table>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Determine the midpoint for each class interval.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Calculate the mean of pocket money given to students per week.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </activity>

    <insight>
        <p>
            <term>Calculating Mean</term>
        </p>
        <p>
            A frequency distribution table can be used to find the mean for grouped data using the formula:
        </p>
        <p>
            <md>
                <mrow>\overline{x}  = \amp \frac{ \sum fx}{ \sum f} </mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
        <p>
            Where:
            <ul>
                <li><p><m>x</m> is the <term>Midpoint</term> of the class interval.</p></li>
                <li><p><m>\overline{x}</m> is the mean.</p></li>
                <li><p><m>\sum fx</m> is the sum of the products of the midpoint and frequency.</p></li>
                <li><p><m>\sum f</m> is the sum of frequencies (total number of data points).</p></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            <term>Midpoint</term> is the average of the lower and upper boundaries of a class interval.
            <md>
                <mrow>\text{Midpoint} = \amp \frac{\text{Lower boundary + Upper boundary}}{2}</mrow>
            </md>
        </p>
    </insight>

    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                A company records the monthly salaries (in KES) of <m>50</m> employees in a frequency distribution table below. Calculate the mean salary.
            </p>
            <table>
                <title>Employee Salaries</title>
                <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                    <row halign="left" header="yes">
                        <cell>Salary Range(KES)</cell>
                        <cell>Number of Employees</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>20,000 - 29,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>30,000 - 39,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>40,000 - 49,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>7</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>50,000 - 59,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>60,000 - 69,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>9</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>70,000 - 79,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>6</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>80,000 - 89,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>90,000 - 99,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>100,000 - 109,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                    </row>
                </tabular>
            </table>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                To calculate the mean, we first find the midpoint (<m>x</m>) of each class and multiply it by the frequency (<m>f</m>).
            </p>
            <table>
                <title>Mean Calculation Table</title>
                <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                    <row halign="left" header="yes">
                        <cell>Salary Range(KES)</cell>
                        <cell>Midpoint (<m>x</m>)</cell>
                        <cell>Frequency (<m>f</m>)</cell>
                        <cell><m>fx</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>20,000 - 29,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>25,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>75,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>30,000 - 39,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>35,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>175,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>40,000 - 49,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>45,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>7</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>315,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>50,000 - 59,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>55,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>550,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>60,000 - 69,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>65,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>9</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>585,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>70,000 - 79,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>75,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>6</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>450,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>80,000 - 89,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>85,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>425,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>90,000 - 99,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>95,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>285,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><m>100,000 - 109,999</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>105,000</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>210,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell><term>Total</term></cell>
                        <cell></cell>
                        <cell><m>\sum f = 50</m></cell>
                        <cell><m>\sum fx = 3,070,000</m></cell>
                    </row>
                </tabular>
            </table>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow>\overline{x}  = \amp \frac{ \sum fx}{ \sum f} </mrow>
                    <mrow>=  \amp \frac{ 3,070,000}{ 50}</mrow>
                    <mrow>=  \amp 61,400</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p>
                Therefore, the mean salary is <m>61,400</m> KES.
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    <!-- Exercises -->
    <exercises xml:id="exercises-mean-grouped">
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A tea factory recorded the weight of tea leaves (in kg) delivered by <m>40</m> small-scale farmers in a single morning.
                </p>
                <table>
                    <title>Tea Weight Deliveries</title>
                    <tabular halign="center" top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                        <row header="yes">
                            <cell>Weight (kg)</cell>
                            <cell>Frequency (Farmers)</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>10 - 19</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>20 - 29</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>8</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>30 - 39</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>15</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>40 - 49</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>50 - 59</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                        </row>
                    </tabular>
                </table>
                <p>
                    Calculate the mean weight of tea leaves delivered per farmer.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    Midpoints (<m>x</m>): <m>14.5, 24.5, 34.5, 44.5, 54.5</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>\sum f = 40</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>\sum fx = (14.5 \times 5) + (24.5 \times 8) + (34.5 \times 15) + (44.5 \times 10) + (54.5 \times 2) = 1330</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Mean <m>= \frac{1330}{40} = 33.25</m> kg.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    A Sacco operating on the Nairobi-Thika route recorded the fares paid by passengers during peak hours on a rainy day.
                </p>
                <table>
                    <title>Fare Distribution</title>
                    <tabular halign="center" top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                        <row header="yes">
                            <cell>Fare (KES)</cell>
                            <cell>No. of Passengers</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>50 - 99</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>20</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>100 - 149</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>45</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>150 - 199</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>30</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>200 - 249</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                        </row>
                    </tabular>
                </table>
                <p>
                    Determine the mean fare paid by the passengers.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    Midpoints (<m>x</m>): <m>74.5, 124.5, 174.5, 224.5</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>\sum f = 100</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>\sum fx = (74.5 \times 20) + (124.5 \times 45) + (174.5 \times 30) + (224.5 \times 5) = 13,450</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Mean <m>= \frac{13,450}{100} = 134.50</m> KES.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    The mathematics department at a High School in Nakuru analyzed the percentage scores of <m>50</m> students in a mock exam.
                </p>
                <table>
                    <title>Maths Scores</title>
                    <tabular halign="center" top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                        <row header="yes">
                            <cell>Marks (%)</cell>
                            <cell>Frequency</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>0 - 20</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>4</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>20 - 40</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>12</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>40 - 60</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>18</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>60 - 80</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>10</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>80 - 100</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>6</m></cell>
                        </row>
                    </tabular>
                </table>
                <p>
                    Calculate the mean score for the class.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    Midpoints (<m>x</m>): <m>10, 30, 50, 70, 90</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>\sum f = 50</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>\sum fx = (10 \times 4) + (30 \times 12) + (50 \times 18) + (70 \times 10) + (90 \times 6) = 2,540</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Mean <m>= \frac{2,540}{50} = 50.8\%</m>.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    An M-Pesa agent in Kisumu recorded the value of transactions performed in the first hour of business.
                </p>
                <table>
                    <title>Transaction Values</title>
                    <tabular halign="center" top="medium" bottom="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
                        <row header="yes">
                            <cell>Value (KES)</cell>
                            <cell>No. of Transactions</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>0 - 1000</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>12</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>1000 - 2000</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>8</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>2000 - 3000</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>6</m></cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>3000 - 4000</m></cell>
                            <cell><m>4</m></cell>
                        </row>
                    </tabular>
                </table>
                <p>
                    Estimate the mean transaction value.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    Midpoints (<m>x</m>): <m>500, 1500, 2500, 3500</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>\sum f = 30</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <m>\sum fx = (500 \times 12) + (1500 \times 8) + (2500 \times 6) + (3500 \times 4) = 47,000</m>
                </p>
                <p>
                    Mean <m>= \frac{47,000}{30} \approx 1,566.67</m> KES.
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>
    </exercises>
